doctype html5
html
  head
    title Twiddly
    link(rel="stylesheet", type="text/css", href="immersive.css")
    script(type="text/javascript", src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.9.1/jquery.min.js")
    script(type="text/javascript", src="js/jquery.easings.min.js")
    script(type="text/javascript", src="js/jquery.slimscroll.min.js")
    script(type="text/javascript", src="js/jquery.fullPage.min.js")
  body
    main
      #fullpage
        section.section#home
          header
            h1 Twiddly
            .caption
              h3 Immerse yourself in gorgeous handpicked content!
              br
              h3 How?
              h3 Just switch on your phone.
        section.section#story1
          .story
            h2 Discover something interesting right on the lockscreen
            .caption No more unlocking your phone, launching an app and waiting for it to load. Our carefully curated content can be perused right on your lockscreen! Something catches your fancy? Just tap and read it right there. With Twiddly, its content first!
        section.section#story2
          .story
            h2 Choose from a list of thoughtfully curated themes
            .caption Do you love cool new gadgets? Or maybe you're looking for a funny video to cheer you up? Twiddly's got your back.
        section.section#story3
          .story
            h2 Bite sized content that packs a punch
            .caption Twiddly carefully chooses your content to be less than 5 minutes long. Waiting for a friend? Long bus ride? Whip out your phone and snack away on the articles and videos waiting for you.
        section.section#founders
          .section-title
            h2 The Founders
          .story
            img(src="images/ranjan.jpg", alt="")
            .caption
              h3 Ranjan Jagannathan
              p Ranjan most recently led customer development, product experiments and analytics for a 500 Startups company, Mygola. Before Mygola, Ranjan was an innovation program manager with Yahoo! India where he designed and ran large scale innovation programs. Ranjan has a degree in Mechanical Engineering and is an alum of Stanford Ignite, an academic program on entrepreneurship by Stanford Graduate School of Business.
          .story
            .caption
              h3 Sanjay Guruprasad
              p Sanjay graduated from IIT Madras in 2012 where he was awarded the Institute Blues for his wide ranging pursuits on campus. He worked at an iBank for a year, but decided to return to Bangalore to chase his startup dream. He worked as a full stack developer at MagnetWorks, developing an alerts system for the iOT startup. He heads 'Enerji' a NodeJS project at Softrade that helps factories move to cleaner fuels. He loves NodeJS, iOS and is very into minimalism.
            img(src="images/sanjay.jpg", alt="")

